The paper deals with the problem of saliency modeling and fixation prediction, which is a common topic in computer vision and machine learning. The use of deep features and ensemble learning also suggests a focus on advanced techniques in these fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of ensemble learning and similarity-based retrieval suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
